comment:
What I really find tragic is that due to Amber Heard playing Mera, the DC Comics super-heroine (one time she had become a super-villainess but that was retconned) is now being highly disliked because of the comic book character's association with Amber Heard in the Aquaman movie. 

It's not fair because while the actress who is currently attached is someone that should be disliked, Mera is not deserving of such hate and the name of the character shouldn't be ruined permanently because of the reputation of the celebrity who is unfortunately connected to Mera. 

She is a good character who has always been a decent partner-in-crime fighting for Aquaman. People should not condemn Aquaman's wife as if the character is only relevant because of Amber Heard. Anyone can play Mera. So disconnecting the art from the artist is necessary.
